Masters in Healthcare Analytics and Operations (MHAO)
Graduates of the Master’s in Healthcare Analytics and Operations (MHAO) program will leverage data and advanced analytical models to evaluate operations and supply chains, generating actionable insights that enhance outcomes in the healthcare sector. This program emphasizes the use of both historical and real-time data to identify trends and optimize processes, ultimately benefiting patients, healthcare professionals, and supply chain partners alike. With a requirement of 30 credit hours, the program is delivered entirely online, making it an excellent choice for full-time professionals in the healthcare industry. The MHAO program curriculum aligns with the competencies required for the Certified Health Data Analyst (CHDA) exam.
The Healthcare Analytics Graduate Certificate equips healthcare professionals with practical data skills to drive informed decisions. This 12-credit online program, ideal for those in or entering healthcare analytics, business intelligence, or health technology, offers focused training without a full master’s degree commitment. Students gain hands-on experience with industry-standard tools, learning to collect, analyze, and communicate healthcare data. Core courses cover analytics, data privacy, and compliance, while electives explore machine learning, operations, and data management. Graduates are prepared to make an immediate impact in performance improvement, financial analysis, population health, and quality and safety reporting.
Master of Real Estate Development (MRED)
The Master of Real Estate Development (MRED) is a 30-credit non-thesis, non-creative component program. The MRED program offers academic training, networking opportunities and collaboration with leading academics and practitioners to solve real world problems. Areas of study include real estate market analysis, finance, investments, leadership and negotiation, fundamentals of the build environment, construction science and urban planning. The curriculum is offered in a convenient format of distance learning and brief campus residencies, making it ideal for the full-time working professional.
Master of Science in Information Systems (MSIS)
The Master of Science in Information Systems (MSIS) program equips students with strong IT skills and a broad understanding of business to design, implement, and manage information systems that support organizational success. The 30-credit curriculum includes business foundation courses, information systems core courses, electives, and a research requirement (creative component). Courses cover areas such as artificial intelligence, big data, cybersecurity, blockchain, and business analytics, giving students the knowledge and tools to innovate and lead in today’s digital economy.
A certificate in enterprise cybersecurity management is also available. The certificate requires a minimum of 12 graduate level approved credits, which may be taken either on-line or face-to-face. For more information on the graduate certificate in enterprise cybersecurity management, please visit: http://catalog.iastate.edu/collegeofbusiness/managementinformationsystems/#graduatecertificatetext.
Master of Entrepreneurship (MEP)
The Master of Entrepreneurship (MEP) is designed to provide students with the knowledge, skills, and practical experience to prepare students to start and manage new business ventures independently — or within an established organization. Students will develop and apply the primary entrepreneurial skills needed to identify and evaluate market opportunities as well as to think creatively to formulate and implement successful strategies for moving a business idea forward. The 30-credit program requires traditional core and elective courses in addition to experiential components designed to help students build experience in real world entrepreneurial tasks and activities.
A certificate in entrepreneurship and innovation is also available. The certificate requires a minimum of 12 graduate level approved credits, which may be taken either on-line or face-to-face. For more information on the graduate certificate in entrepreneurship and innovation, please visit: http://catalog.iastate.edu/collegeofbusiness/entrepreneurship/#graduatecertificatetext.
Master of Science in Supply Chain Management (MS SCM)
The Master of Science in Supply Chain Management (MS SCM) is designed to provide high-quality professional training to students. Students graduating from this program are expected to develop into highly qualified supply chain professionals who possess advanced managerial and analytical skills to make sound supply chain decisions and lead supply chain improvement initiatives. With a requirement of 30 credit hours, the program is delivered entirely online, making it an excellent choice for undergraduate students entering their final year at Iowa State as well as full-time professionals with some initial work experience.
A certificate in supply chain management is also available. The certificate requires a minimum of 12 graduate level approved credits, which may only be taken on-line. For more information on the graduate certificate in supply chain management, please visit: http://catalog.iastate.edu/collegeofbusiness/supplychainmanagement/#graduatecertificatetext.
A certificate in Quantitative Principles in Business is offered by the Ivy College of Business. The 15-credit certificate, which incorporates coursework from Quantitative Business Analysis, Financial Valuation, and Financial Markets, also provides students a choice of electives in related business fields. The certificate enhances a student’s career prospects with a credential that demonstrates quantitative and analytical skills competencies. Students who achieve a B or higher average in the certificate can stack this certificate with the Leadership in Business certificate (15 credits) and one additional Ivy Graduate Certificate (12-15 credits) to earn the Professional Master of Business Administration degree. For more information on the graduate certificate in Quantitative Principles in Business, visit: https://www.ivybusiness.iastate.edu/academics/graduate-programs/graduate-certificates/.
Strong leadership skills differentiate high-performing professionals and are increasingly valued by employers in all industries. The Leadership in Business graduate certificate offers a flexible and stackable pathway for busy professionals to build essential management and leadership skills. Students in the certificate will develop valuable leadership competencies that prepare them for management positions with greater responsibility and impact. The certificate requires three core courses (Professional Responsibility in Business and Society, Strategic Management, and Leadership) and two elective courses from approved options in accounting, management, marketing, supply chain management, and management information systems. For professionals looking to build their leadership expertise and gain a competitive edge, the Leadership in Business certificate provides the knowledge and credentials to accelerate career trajectory. Students who achieve a B or higher average in the certificate can stack this certificate with the Quantitative Principles in Business certificate (15 credits) and one additional Ivy Graduate Certificate (12-15 credits) to earn the Professional Master of Business Administration degree. For more information on the graduate certificate in Leadership in Business, please visit: https://www.ivybusiness.iastate.edu/academics/graduate-programs/graduate-certificates/
The Ivy College of Business participates in the following graduate level interdepartmental programs: Cyber Security, Engineering Management, Human Computer Interaction, and Seed Technology and Business.
PhD in Business and Technology
The Ivy College of Business offers graduate work leading to the Doctor of Philosophy degree in business and technology, with one of six specializations—entrepreneurship (ENTSP), finance, (FIN), information systems and business analytics (ISBA), management (MGMT), marketing (MKT), or supply chain management (SCM). Departments in the college (Finance, Management and Entrepreneurship, Marketing, Supply Chain Management, and Information Systems and Business Analytics), along with select other departments from across campus cooperate in providing coursework toward this degree. The program prepares individuals for academic careers in research, teaching, and public service at institutions of higher learning in the United States and other countries. The program consists of seminars in content areas, statistics, and research methodology in the first two years. After passing comprehensive exams, students will focus on their dissertation.
The standard length of this 74-credit program is five years. All work, including the dissertation, must be done in residence (on campus).
For more details or application information contact the Graduate Programs office in the Ivy College of Business or visit: https://www.ivybusiness.iastate.edu/academics/phd-program/.